{"version": "https://jsonfeed.org/version/1.1", "title": "Apache Iceberg\u2122", "home_page_url": "https://iceberg.apache.org/", "feed_url": "https://iceberg.apache.org/feed_json_created.json", "description": "Blogs for Apache Iceberg", "icon": "https://iceberg.apache.org/assets/images/Iceberg-logo.svg", "authors": [], "language": "en", "items": [{"id": "https://iceberg.apache.org/blog/apache-iceberg-cpp-0.2.0-release/", "url": "https://iceberg.apache.org/blog/apache-iceberg-cpp-0.2.0-release/", "title": "Apache Iceberg C++ 0.2.0 Release", "content_html": "<!--\n - Licensed to the Apache Software Foundation (ASF) under one or more\n - contributor license agreements.  See the NOTICE file distributed with\n - this work for additional information regarding copyright ownership.\n - The ASF licenses this file to You under the Apache License, Version 2.0\n - (the \"License\"); you may not use this file except in compliance with\n - the License.  You may obtain a copy of the License at\n -\n -   http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n -\n - Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n - distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n - WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n - See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n - limitations under the License.\n -->\n\n<p>The Apache Iceberg community is pleased to announce the 0.2.0 release of Apache Iceberg C++. This release includes <a href=\"https://github.com/apache/iceberg-cpp/compare/v0.1.0...v0.2.0\">over 200 merged pull requests</a> from 23 distinct contributors.</p>\n<p>The release notes below are not exhaustive and only expose selected highlights of the release. Many other bugfixes and improvements have been made: we refer you to the <a href=\"https://github.com/apache/iceberg-cpp/releases/tag/v0.2.0\">complete changelog</a> for details.</p>", "image": null, "date_modified": "2026-01-29T06:58:23+00:00", "date_published": "2026-01-26T00:00:00+00:00", "authors": [{"name": "Apache Iceberg PMC"}], "tags": ["release"]}, {"id": "https://iceberg.apache.org/blog/announcing-iceberg-summit-2026/", "url": "https://iceberg.apache.org/blog/announcing-iceberg-summit-2026/", "title": "Announcing Iceberg Summit 2026", "content_html": "<!--\n - Licensed to the Apache Software Foundation (ASF) under one or more\n - contributor license agreements.  See the NOTICE file distributed with\n - this work for additional information regarding copyright ownership.\n - The ASF licenses this file to You under the Apache License, Version 2.0\n - (the \"License\"); you may not use this file except in compliance with\n - the License.  You may obtain a copy of the License at\n -\n -   http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n -\n - Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n - distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n - WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n - See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n - limitations under the License.\n -->\n\n<p><strong>Iceberg Summit is officially coming back in 2026!</strong></p>\n<p>Mark your calendars! On <strong>April 8 and 9, 2026</strong>, the Apache Iceberg community will gather once again in <strong>San Francisco</strong> at the Marriott Marquis for two full days dedicated to all things Iceberg. </p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://www.icebergsummit.org/#register\">Register now</a></strong> to reserve your spot!</p>", "image": null, "date_modified": "2026-01-29T06:58:23+00:00", "date_published": "2026-01-10T00:00:00+00:00", "authors": [{"name": "Apache Iceberg PMC"}], "tags": ["announcement"]}]}